            <p class="title_dec">#３ Demanding Properties</p> <br>
            In Los Santos, real estate isn't just about bricks and mortar, it's about status.  From luxurious mansions overlooking the city to sprawling estates in the countryside, we've got the perfect place for you to call home. 
            Just like Michael, Franklin, and Trevor, you can live the high life and own a piece of Los Santos that reflects your success.So come on down, and find the perfect 
            property to fit your lifestyle.We've got something for everyone, 
            from the humble beginnings to the penthouse suite.<br><br>
            </div>

            <img src="" class="image-content" alt="">
            
            <div class="contentfont">
            <p class="title_dec">#４ Hire Mafia</p> <br>
            <p class="desc_cont">In Los Santos, problems have solutions.  And when you need something done right, you need professionals.  We're not talking about your typical, run-of-the-mill thugs.  We're talking about the best.  The most discreet.  
            The most… effective.</p><br><br>
            </div>

            <img src="" class="image-content" alt="">
            

        </div>





    </section>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', (event) => {
            const successMessage = "{{successMessage}}";
            const errorMessage = "{{errorMessage}}";
        });
        let text = document.getElementById('text');
            // let leaf = document.getElementById('leaf');
        let hill1 = document.getElementById('hill1');
        let hill4 = document.getElementById('hill4');
        let hill3 = document.getElementById('hill3');
        let hill5 = document.getElementById('hill5');
        let hill2 = document.getElementById('hill2');

        window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
            let value = window.scrollY;
        
            text.style.marginTop = value * 2.5 + 'px';
            // leaf.style.top = value * -1.5 +'px';
            // leaf.style.left = value * 1.5 +'px';
            hill5.style.left = value * 1 +'px';
        
            hill3.style.left = value * 1.5 +'px';
        
            hill4.style.left = value * -1.5 +'px';
        
            hill2.style.left = value * -1 +'px';
        
            // hill1.style.top = value * 1.5 +'px';
        })
    </script>

    <script>
        var audio = new Audio();
        audio.src='audio/click.mp3';
        var error = new Audio();
        error.src = 'audio/error.mp3';
    </script>
</body>
</html>